gomodel:SYNGO_2221  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0099061 replaced by GO:0098839" , "Rationale: Immunoparticles for LRRC4C were mostly detected postsynaptically in the vicinity of the postsynaptic density of dendritic spines in SLM.\n\n2/1/2018 Pim\n- LRRC4C is referred to as NGL1 in this paper.\n- Literal: \"Immunoparticles for NGL1 and NGL2 were mostly detected postsynaptically in the vicinity of the postsynaptic density of dendritic spines in SLM and SR, respectively.\" Note: 'SLM' means 'stratum lacunosum moleculare'\n- Based on the known transmembrane topology of the protein, the \"integral component of ... membrane\" term was chosen.. Experimental description: Materials and Methods\nElectron microscopy\nFor post-embedding iEM, adult mice were deeply anesthetized." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-5518-6584" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6194-9648" ;
        dc:date           "2024-03-14" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_2221" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

